articles.author: Adam Wren
articles.title: Vance heads to Indiana after Republicans warn White House of stalled redistricting push - Politico
articles.description: It marks the vice president's second trip to the Hoosier State over the remapping effort.
articles.content: Indiana Gov. Mike Braun, a Republican, conveyed his concerns about the redistricting efforts chances in the state Senate to the White House last week, two people familiar with those discussions told … [+4052 chars]
